The paper deals with coding for channels with insertion and deletion errors, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The segmentation assumption is a structural constraint that can be seen as a form of data structure (cs.DS) or algorithmic constraint (cs.DC). The proposed code constructions and decoding algorithms involve combinatorial and probabilistic techniques (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents an upper bound on the rate of any zero-error code, which is a theoretical result that could be of interest to researchers in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
